#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 11 is primarily philosophical and meditative, with a practical component
  (the metal meditations) that is genuinely preparatory for Year Three rather than
  performative. The metal meditations are non-negotiable deliverables — not because
  they produce a measurable result, but because they establish the perceptual
  baseline without which Year Three's mineral work operates in the dark. A student
  who cannot describe the qualitative difference between sitting with lead and
  sitting with copper has not developed the perceptual sensitivity that Year Three
  demands. The safety requirements for lead must be confirmed before Month 11 begins.
]

